/* <orly/lang_tests/general/variants_storage.orly>

   End-to-end test for issue #95 (sum types / tagged unions): a single
   variant value round-trips through storage.

   A variant value is stored as a single-key record (`Integer(7)` ->
   `<{.Integer: 7}>`); the call-site `::(T)` annotation drives
   reconstruction as a variant on read (the Sabot::TToNativeVisitor
   specialization emitted for each generated variant struct). This proves
   the whole stack: the orlyscript surface (variant type + constructor,
   Phase 3 M1), `::(T)`-driven sabot read-back (Phase 3 M2), and the
   engine layers from Phases 0-2 (type node, var value + ordering,
   code_gen struct + AsVar).

   It uses a 2-arm flat variant `<| Integer(int) | Deleted |>` and asserts
   round-tripping with `==`/`!=` only -- variant equality was wired end to
   end in Phases 0-1. Destructuring of a stored, read-back variant (the
   `is <Tag>` predicate and the `.<Tag>` guarded payload accessor, Phase 3
   M4) is exercised in the sibling variants_destructure.orly.

   SETS of variants are a separate, deeper case (issue #96): a sabot set
   needs a homogeneous element type, but differently-tagged variants
   stored as single-key records are heterogeneous, so set-of-variant
   storage needs a dedicated variant sabot type. See variants_set_storage
   (xfail, #96).

   Copyright 2010-2026 Atomic Kismet Company

   Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");
   you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.
   You may obtain a copy of the License at

     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

   Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software
   distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,
   WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.
   See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
   limitations under the License. */

read_var = (*<[n]>::(<| Integer(int) | Deleted |>)) where {
  n = given::(int);
};

/* Single variant value (typed arm) round-trips through storage. */
with {
  <[400]> <- <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Integer(7);
} test {
  t1: read_var(.n: 400) == <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Integer(7);
  /* A different arm is not equal. */
  t2: read_var(.n: 400) != <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Deleted;
  /* A different payload of the same arm is not equal. */
  t3: read_var(.n: 400) != <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Integer(8);
};

/* Single variant value (tag-only arm) round-trips through storage. */
with {
  <[401]> <- <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Deleted;
} test {
  t4: read_var(.n: 401) == <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Deleted;
  t5: read_var(.n: 401) != <| Integer(int) | Deleted |>.Integer(0);
};
